  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-bacon-alfredo-sauce-with-mushroom-tortelloni/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your<strong> bacon lardons </strong>and cook for 4-5 min or until beginning to crisp</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-bacon-alfredo-sauce-with-mushroom-tortelloni/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>portobello mushroom tortelloni</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the tortelloni for 3-4 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>tortelloni</strong>, reserving a cup of the<strong> starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-bacon-alfredo-sauce-with-mushroom-tortelloni/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Reboil a kettle</p><p>Peel and slice (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>sliced garlic </strong>to the pan with the bacon and cook for 1 min further or until fragrant</p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk to make sure they don't burn!</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-bacon-alfredo-sauce-with-mushroom-tortelloni/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve your<strong> stock mix </strong>in 50ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[75ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[100ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>and stir in your <strong>soft cheese </strong>– this is your <strong>creamy stock</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>creamy stock</strong> and <strong>half</strong> your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese </strong>(save the rest for garnish!) to the pan with the bacon and cook for 1-2 min or until starting to thicken – this is your <strong>creamy bacon Alfredo sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-bacon-alfredo-sauce-with-mushroom-tortelloni/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the sauce is thickening, wash your <strong>spinach</strong>, then add<strong> </strong>to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water </strong>all over it so that it starts to wilt</p><p>Rinse the<strong> wilted spinach</strong> under <strong>cold running water</strong> until it's cool</p><p>Once cool, squeeze as much water out of the <strong>spinach</strong> as you can, then chop it roughly</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-bacon-alfredo-sauce-with-mushroom-tortelloni/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained tortelloni </strong>and <strong>chopped wilted spinach </strong>to the creamy<strong> </strong>bacon<strong> </strong>Alfredo<strong> </strong>sauce<strong> </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Tip: Add a splash of starchy pasta water if your sauce is looking a little dry</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-bacon-alfredo-sauce-with-mushroom-tortelloni/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>creamy bacon Alfredo tortelloni </strong>topped with the <strong>remaining grated Italian hard cheese</strong></p><p>Season with a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
